2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with cache-aided wireless communication scenarios, which are a subfield of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the use of caching in wireless networks, which is a topic relevant to social and information networks. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a scheme based on the separation principle, which is a fundamental concept in data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with content delivery and non-content communication, which are topics relevant to multimedia.
